Here's the full program:

```csharp
using System.Text.Json;

var person = new Person("john", 30);

var options = new JsonSerializerOptions
{
    PropertyNamingPolicy = JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase,
    WriteIndented = true
};

string json = JsonSerializer.Serialize(person, options);
Console.WriteLine(json);

public record Person(string name, int age);
```

**Output:**
```json
{
  "Name": "john",
  "Age": 30
}
```

The key is `JsonNamingPolicy.PascalCase` — a built-in policy (added in .NET 8) that converts your lowercase parameter names (`name`, `age`) to PascalCase (`Name`, `Age`) in the serialized JSON. No custom naming-policy class needed.
